node.text: Short film by @taylorglenn | We all know people whose dedication to a passion or purpose inspires us deeply. Gannett Horn's (@surfasaur) focus on his sport and love for its community embodies the best in each of us. This short film is a testament to Gannett and those who motivate us to work harder at the things we love. #riversurfing Production by @apresvisuals

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by National Geographic Adventure on September 07, 2021. May be an image of nature and sky.

node.text: Photo by @paulzizkaphoto / Crimson cliffs frame a star-filled sky and the Milky Way on a previous trip to Mongolia. Dreaming about exploring more of this incredible landscape someday!

Photos and videos by @taylorglenn / A few weeks ago, @ben.blanton and I scored an incredible day in the Tetons. We climbed the Upper Exum Ridge of the Grand Teton in “spring” conditions. It was one of the quietest days I have experienced in the mountains. You could hear a pin drop all day long and we saw only one other climber in Garnet Canyon. So surreal! I have spent a lot of time in these hills, and this day was one that will stand out among so many wonderful climbs. These images were made with my smartphone, which I love using in these situations because it’s easy to operate and cuts down on the bulk of carrying a bigger camera. Follow @taylorglenn for more from the Tetons and beyond. #Wyoming #Tetons #Climbing

node.text: Video by @guillermocerveraphoto / One of the hardest triathlons in the world, Ironman Lanzarote consists of a 2.4-mile (3.8-km) swim, a 112-mile (180.2-km) bicycle ride and a marathon 26.22-mile (42.2-km) run. Incredible the effort and the pace these athletes can reach. It was an honor to be able to film this event. On the bike @boris_stein #lanzarote #canaryislands

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by National Geographic Adventure on September 06, 2021. May be an image of nature.

node.text: Photo by @michaelclarkphoto / Savannah Cummins on Anunnaki (5.11+) at the Optimator Wall in Indian Creek, Utah. This image was created in collaboration with Ted Hesser, another stellar adventure photographer. Ted climbed up into the top of the alcove above the climb with a giant flash, which was triggered by the transmitter on top of my camera. #indiancreek #utah #rockclimbing

node.text: Photo by @brittmumma / Arguably the best event of the rodeo, the Indian Relays never lack in excitement. Image taken at the 2021 Sheridan WYO Rodeo.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by National Geographic Adventure on September 05, 2021. May be an image of nature and sky.

node.text: Photo by Mylo Fowler @navajomylo / Above the Rio Grande spans the fifth-highest bridge in the U.S. Flying above it with Chris Dahl-Bredine (@shotsfromabove) gives the vast landscape a completely different perspective. Flying below, above and through the clouds was quite smooth and chaotic in terms of emotions. For more of the Southwest, follow @navajomylo

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by National Geographic Adventure on September 04, 2021. May be an image of nature and sky.

node.text: Photo by Chris Boyes @christurtleboyes / Take yourself to places you have dreamt about and they will inspire you to dream some more. And then, make sure you give yourself time to realize why they were dreamt at all. Sitting next to the Luapula River of the upper Congo catchment in Zambia, a vivid dream come true. Taking time to contemplate the sheer magnitude of this water's journey ahead, the vital conservation goals that need to be achieved over the next decade, how small everything we know is compared with the universe out there, and yet how critical every little piece of it all is to the whole! Let's value our natural world; we really need every bit of it!

node.text: Video by @coreyrichproductions / "At the same time that we are earnest to explore and learn all things, we require that all things be mysterious and unexplorable, that land and sea be indefinitely wild ... We can never have enough of nature.”—Henry David Thoreau. Here's to being a respectful tourist and a fierce protector of these amazing wild places. Exploring the South Island of New Zealand with @chrisburkard.
